# Combined Sales Data
__________________________

The file contains the transformed and combined data from the sources:
Sales Data Folder:
        a. Dcart(Subfolder) : 7 Excel files of Sales Data
        b. D2C(Subfolder)   : 7 Csv files of Sales Data with 2 Sheets each as per Sub - channels
                         : 1  Excel file of Nile Sales Data with 7 sheets as per Months

ETL Process: 
==================================================================================================
1. Importing data from multiple Folders

2. Transforming Binary into Sheet and From Sheet to Table

3. Create Query (List) for Column Transformation 

4. Promote headers, Keep Required columns, Rename Columns, Change Data Types

5.Combining tables from different files and sheets

6. Validating Data Completeness and Quality

(ETL Steps)
=============================================================================================
As all the column names are identical across the files hence created 3 lists for only the required columns:
           
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
| List name               Purpose                                                        Query                                                                                                            |
|_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________|        
| 1.ALL Columns      Existing Columns Names   |    = {"Sales_Date" ,"Delivery_Date","SKU_Code","Qty","Unit_Price","Line_Amount","From_Location","To_Location","Channel","Sub_Channel","Delivery_Type",    |
|                                             |   "Courier","City_Tier","Category","Order_ID","Customer_ID","Payment_Method","Is_Returned"}                                                               |
|                                             |                                                                                                                                                           |
|_____________________________________________|___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________|
|                                             |                                                                                                                                                           |                                                                                                                                                                                                    
| 2.AllNew Columns   Renamed Columns          | = {"Sales Date","Delivery Date","SKU_Code", "Quantity","Unit Price","Sales Amount","From_Location","To_Location","Channel","Sub-Channel","Delivery_Type", |
|                                             | "Courier","City_Tier","Category","Order_ID","Customer_ID","Payment_Method","Is_Returned"}                                                                 |
|                                             |                                                                                                                                                           |
|_____________________________________________|___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________|
|                                             |                                                                                                                                                           |
| 3.RenameMapping   Created list for          |  =  List.Zip({#"ALL Columns",#"AllNew Columns"})                                                                                                          |
|                   mapping renamed columns   |                                                                                                                                                           |
|                                             |                                                                                                                                                           |
|_____________________________________________|___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________|
|                                             |                                                                                                                                                           |
| 4.DataTypes       Determining Data Types    |  =    {{"Sales Date",  type date},{"Delivery Date",  type date},{"SKU_Code", type text},{"Quantity", Int64.Type},{"Unit Price",Int64.Type},               |
|                                             |         {"Sales Amount",Int64.Type},{"From_Location",type text},{"To_Location",type text},{"Channel",type text},                                          |
|                                             |         {"Sub-Channel",type text},{"Delivery_Type",type text},{"Courier",type text},{"City_Tier",type text},{"Category",type text},                       |
|                                             |         {"Order_ID",type text},{"Customer_ID",type text},{"Payment_Method",type text},{"Is_Returned",Int64.Type}}                                         |
|_____________________________________________|___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________|

Dcart(Subfolder):
====================================================================================================================
Source Files:

DCart_Sales_2025-01.xlsx
DCart_Sales_2025-02.xlsx
DCart_Sales_2025-03.xlsx
DCart_Sales_2025-04.xlsx
DCart_Sales_2025-05.xlsx
DCart_Sales_2025-06.xlsx
DCart_Sales_2025-07.xlsx
======================================================================================================================
 --Converted Binary to Excel workbook, promoted first row as headers, kept only the Content column consisting Tables
 --Removed unwanted column and renamed them
======================================================================================================================
Query:
1. let
    Source = Folder.Files("C:\Users\Dyuti Mazumder\Downloads\Data Cleaning (Chandeep)\Case Data\Sales Data\DCart"),
    Custom1 = Table.SelectColumns( Table.TransformColumns(Source,{"Content", each Excel.Workbook(_,true)}),"Content"), //Converted Binary to Excel workbook, promoted first row as headers, kept only the Content column consisting Tables
    #"Expanded Content" = Table.ExpandTableColumn(Custom1, "Content", {"Name", "Data", "Item", "Kind", "Hidden"}, {"Name", "Data", "Item", "Kind", "Hidden"}), //Expanded Tables
    Data = Table.RenameColumns ( Table.SelectColumns(Table.Combine( #"Expanded Content"[Data]),#"ALL Columns"),RenameMapping) //Removed unwanted column and renamed them
in
    Data

D2C (Subfolder):
======================================================================================================================
Source Files: 

sales_D2C_2025-01.csv
sales_D2C_2025-02.csv
sales_D2C_2025-03.csv
sales_D2C_2025-04.csv
sales_D2C_2025-05.csv
sales_D2C_2025-06.csv
sales_D2C_2025-07.csv
======================================================================================================================
--Converted table into list for making the headers and columns dynamic, kept only required columns and  renamed columns
--Changed datatype as per "Datatypes" list
--Removed rows with error from all columns
======================================================================================================================
Query:

let
    Source = Folder.Files("C:\Users\Dyuti Mazumder\Downloads\Data Cleaning (Chandeep)\Case Data\Sales Data\D2C"),
    Custom1 = Table.SelectColumns( Table.AddColumn(Source, "Custom", each Csv.Document([Content])),"Custom"),// Added custom column Converted Binary to Table

    #"Combine n expand" = Table.RenameColumns( Table.SelectColumns( Table.PromoteHeaders(Table.Combine(Custom1[Custom]),[PromoteAllScalars=true]),#"ALL Columns"),RenameMapping), 
// Convert table into list for making the headers and columns dynamic, kept only required columns and  renamed columns

    #"Changed Type" = Table.TransformColumnTypes(#"Combine n expand",DataTypes),// Changed datatype as per "Datatypes" list
    #"Removed Errors" = Table.RemoveRowsWithErrors(#"Changed Type",#"AllNew Columns")// Removed columns with error from all columns
in
    #"Removed Errors"


Source File: Nile_Sales_YTD.xlsx

Sheets:
Nile_Sales_2025-07
Nile_Sales_2025-06
Nile_Sales_2025-05
Nile_Sales_2025-04
Nile_Sales_2025-03
Nile_Sales_2025-02
Nile_Sales_2025-01
_xlnm._FilterDatabase

====================================================================================================================
--Filtered unwanted sheet : _xlnm._FilterDatabase
--Made the headers and columns dynamic to update automatically when new data is loaded.
--Renamed Columns as AllNew Columns list
--Changed column type as per datatype mapping list
====================================================================================================================
Query:

let
    Source = Excel.Workbook(File.Contents("C:\Users\Dyuti Mazumder\Downloads\Data Cleaning (Chandeep)\Case Data\Sales Data\Nile_Sales_YTD.xlsx"), null, true),
    #"Filtered Rows" = Table.SelectRows(Source, each ([Name] <> "_xlnm._FilterDatabase")),
    Data = Table.RemoveRowsWithErrors( Table.TransformColumnTypes(Table.RenameColumns( Table.PromoteHeaders( Table.Combine( #"Filtered Rows"[Data]),[PromoteAllScalars=true]),RenameMapping),DataTypes),#"AllNew Columns")
in
    Data

Combined Sales Data: New query
======================================================================================================================
= Table.TransformColumnTypes( Table.Combine({DCart, D2C, #"Nile_Sales_2025-01"}),DataTypes) // Combined all file data after ETL
